That's it. The defendant doesn't necessarily have to use the words 有罪
or 無罪 (in fact, I've heard that some defense lawyers specifically
instruct their clients not to utter these words), but he is expected
to make his stance clear. It almost always goes something like this:

事実に間違いありません (pleads guilty)

私はやっていません (pleads not guility) or 私はAをやりましたが、Bはしていません (partial)

